{"TopicId":194824,"ForumId":66,"TopicTitle":"KSP Loading...: Sharing Horizons with ESA","CreatedByName":"UomoCapra","CreatedById":167737,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-17T19:15:19Z","PageNum":4,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"VoidCosmos","CreatedById":192336,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T17:16:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592500424\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179192\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boyster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Boyster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill the comets appear in current savegames as well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"matteeeo","CreatedById":89209,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T17:41:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805258\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592490861\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298962\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Streetwind\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Streetwind said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe former - and I suspect it\u0027s not an issue of willingness on Squad\u0027s part, but rather a hard limitation of the game engine that makes it impossible to assign gravity and spheres of influence to anything not permanently on rails.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[...]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EAdd one or two comets to the Kerbin system as fixed, permanently on-rails, celestial objects. Their orbits would be designed so that they never come near any other celestial body. They would have gravity, and a sphere of influence, and their own names, and so on. They would work exactly like Gilly does, except with perhaps even less gravity. You would always have exactly these one or two, with exactly the same model and texture and parameters. No more would ever spawn, and there is no discovery mechanic. You could not move them, or claw into them. \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAdd procedurally generated comets that use the asteroid base mechanic. There will be an infinite amount of them, given enough time, and they will gradually appear and disappear again (if ignored). This provides unique challenges that are slightly different in every playthrough, or even in different phases of the same playthrough. They can have different shapes and sizes and textures. They can be intercepted and moved to new orbits by the player, and given custom names, and/or incorporated into space stations. They are allowed to enter and exit spheres of influence like a spacecraft does, so If they happen to cross a sphere of influence other than the Sun\u0027s, their orbit will be believably deflected by that gravity well. But they will not have gravity or spheres of influence of their own.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nPick one. You cannot have both. And so, Squad made their choice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree with you on the motivations, but I don\u0027t see why one option must exclude the other. Although I don\u0027t know about the implementation challenges they would have to face, they could add one or two very big permanent comets with their own stabe trajectories and SOIs, with a small enough mass to provide little gravity but still high enough to justify making them unmoveable, and then have smaller ones treated as bigger asteroids.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut in any case, I wouldn\u0027t dare to go complain with the devs going one way over the other, I appreciate the work they are doing and can\u0027t wait for the update \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhelperdude","CreatedById":204462,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T17:48:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592500424\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179192\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Boyster\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n33 minutes ago, Boyster said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAwesome!!!Cant wait!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill the comets appear in current savegames as well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWill they be\u00A0in tracking station or only when taking missions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSry if these questions\u00A0have been answered before \u003Cspan\u003E:p.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes and both\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ItsJustLuci","CreatedById":181134,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T19:20:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223804944\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592435159\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196943\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceFace545\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, SpaceFace545 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndon\u0027t bet on it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntrust me, I\u0027m not. I just understand that it would be a relatively easy thing to do that would enable a massive feature, and I felt like sharing that with the community \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Souptime","CreatedById":204451,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T19:31:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHOW MANY TIMES ARE YA GONNA UPDATE THE POODLE?!?!?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Klapaucius","CreatedById":181256,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T20:08:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is just looking better and better!\u00A0 I love that comets are now in the game and the flag thing is seriously cool!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuestion: Are the comets behaving like asteroids or like planets in the game? In other words, are they randomly generated on each load or will we have a defined number of them that are always in the same orbits?\u00A0 (Sorry if this was mentioned and I somehow missed it).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-06-18T20:09:32Z\u0022 title=\u002206/18/2020 08:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJune 18, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Klapaucius\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GrandProtectorDark","CreatedById":183946,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T20:18:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805433\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592510928\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181256\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Klapaucius\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Klapaucius said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre the comets behaving like asteroids or like planets in the game?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClaws can only grab parts. So I highly guess those are gonna be parts too (asteroids are also parts btw)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tkw","CreatedById":142638,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-18T20:43:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0i think some parts in your mods has existed.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yellowburn10","CreatedById":107558,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T02:08:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery nice stuff indeed. This release is scheduled for July 1st, correct?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T02:35:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805632\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592532520\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107558\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yellowburn10\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n25 minutes ago, Yellowburn10 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis release is scheduled for July 1st, correct?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCorrect!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223804821\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592421319\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167737\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022UomoCapra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/17/2020 at 3:15 PM, UomoCapra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunching on July 1st, \u003Cem\u003EKerbal Space Program 1.10: Shared Horizons\u003C/em\u003E is special in many ways.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xurkitree","CreatedById":187694,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T02:36:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003Einsert parts are cool opinion\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut aw man, I was hoping for a new celestial body comet, that would have its own elliptical orbit. I think it\u0027d be really cool to have one place to go and plant flags on, and the procedurally generated comets can add to the other bodies. That would be really neat and good new content. But i\u0027m okay with what\u0027s been given honestly - kinda dig the MTM probe\u0027s blast shield like orientation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yellowburn10","CreatedById":107558,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T03:39:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805638\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592534102\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCorrect!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSweet! That means there\u0027s less than two weeks to go. I\u0027ll be waiting in anticipation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SnacklessKerbal","CreatedById":189037,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T05:37:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan we mix and match the fairing bases with the fairings?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T06:19:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805698\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592545079\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189037\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SnacklessKerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, SnacklessKerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan we mix and match the fairing bases with the fairings?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, the fairings are not actual parts. Only the fairing bases are. And they are simply getting additional variants.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"noobsrtoast","CreatedById":65729,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T07:23:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso im assuming then the comets will count as parts that dont have gravity? thats unfortunate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T09:27:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf comets had gravity, one could make a double comet with double spiral tail...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T09:39:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592551389\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002265729\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022noobsrtoast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, noobsrtoast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso im assuming then the comets will count as parts that dont have gravity? thats unfortunate.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d have found a static comet that\u0027s on rails to be a disappointment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThough it\u0027d be nice to have both. Like how we have asteroids and also Gilly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-06-19T09:39:48Z\u0022 title=\u002206/19/2020 09:39  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJune 19, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Superfluous J\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T10:00:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805774\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592559566\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d have found a static comet that\u0027s on rails to be a disappointment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA major one or two, like the Halley\u0027s one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd random craft-with-gravity ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wish the craft-with-gravity would be also implemented to make gravitationally stable pairs of asteroids or to orbit a death star.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso we don\u0027t know, maybe Voyagers already have their own satellites or even rings.\u003Cbr\u003E\nA million years later a Voyager will pass through some dust cloud, destabilize it, and become the seed of a new solar system, with Voyager in the center of the protostar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-06-19T10:01:23Z\u0022 title=\u002206/19/2020 10:01  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJune 19, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T10:32:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805781\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592560822\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso we don\u0027t know, maybe Voyagers already have their own satellites or even rings.\u003Cbr\u003E\nA million years later a Voyager will pass through some dust cloud, destabilize it, and become the seed of a new solar system, with Voyager in the center of the protostar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot-1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002247.69\u0022 height=\u0022382\u0022 width=\u0022801\u0022 src=\u0022https://i2.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/screenshot-1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"panzer1b","CreatedById":95108,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T12:41:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone know how big the comets will be?\u00A0 I already have a rather overkill supertanker that doubles up as a class-E tug, but im wondering if i shoud make something even bigger or just reuse what aint broke if the comets will be similar mass?\u00A0 Sorta doesnt look too big from the picture, but no idea what the size variation would be...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFace545","CreatedById":196943,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T13:34:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805795\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592562742\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i2.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/screenshot-1.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot-1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002247.69\u0022 height=\u0022382\u0022 width=\u0022801\u0022 src=\u0022https://i2.wp.com/media.boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/screenshot-1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nV\u2019ger\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Quoniam Kerman","CreatedById":181893,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T13:49:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisturbiing some asteroids trajectory even by a milimeter could mean the difference between the birth/death of a potential civilization on some planet... So Voyager could either become the main event for some people without even knowing they have been influenced by it. It is however highly unlikely to happen...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd Voyagers are too light to have their own satellites and rings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-06-19T13:51:14Z\u0022 title=\u002206/19/2020 01:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJune 19, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Quoniam Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T14:04:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592570465\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002295108\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022panzer1b\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, panzer1b said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022 data-gramm=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone know how big the comets will be?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn scientific terms???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBigger than a breadbox...\u003Cbr\u003E\nSmaller than Gilly...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"releansol","CreatedById":153963,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T14:33:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s all free...again... Where are the times we thanked SQUAD at least\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTHANKS KSP-TEAM!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-06-19T15:57:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223805854\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022194824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221592574589\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181893\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Quoniam Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Quoniam Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd Voyagers are too light to have their own satellites and rings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHill sphere\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224532f0ae55e77a1912c0de011353465277aefa33\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002243.22\u0022 height=\u002251\u0022 width=\u0022118\u0022 src=\u0022https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4532f0ae55e77a1912c0de011353465277aefa33\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\na ~= 100 AU ~= 1.5*10\u003Csup\u003E13\u003C/sup\u003E m.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nM ~= 2*10\u003Csup\u003E30\u003C/sup\u003E kg.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nm ~= 720 kg.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nr ~= 1.5*10\u003Csup\u003E13\u003C/sup\u003E m * (720 kg / (3 * 2*10\u003Csup\u003E30\u003C/sup\u003E kg))\u003Csup\u003E1/3\u003C/sup\u003E ~= 7400 m.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, currently Voyager can have satellites inside ~7 km radius.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen it gets to the 2 ly distance from the Sun, it will be ~ 10 000 km (because of the Sun) or ~20 000 (because of the Galaxy), i.e. LEO-sized.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, Voyager can easily form a microgalaxy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}